  "narrative": {
    "intro": "NAICS 561210 federal contract obligations total $30.3B in FY2026 to date. Obligations fell 18.2% year over year. The market delivered 10,509 awards so far this fiscal year, with an average award size of $2.9M. Year-to-year totals peaked earlier in the decade at $37.5B in FY24 and recorded $37.1B in FY25; FY23, FY22, and FY21 were $36.5B, $34.1B, and $31.8B respectively. The FY2026 to date total of $30.3B is lower than each of the previous five fiscal years listed. Large departmental concentrations are evident in the buyer list, with a single agency accounting for the majority of FY2026 to date obligations. The top vendors list shows several multi-billion-dollar incumbents active in this NAICS, alongside smaller firms with obligations in the hundreds of millions. These figures reflect contract obligations only and represent fiscal year to date totals for the current year.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies are the largest buyers of NAICS 561210 services?",
        "body": "The Department of Energy is the largest buyer, with $23.2B in FY2026 to date obligations. The Department of Defense follows with $4.4B, and the General Services Administration accounts for $534M. Other notable buyers include the Department of Homeland Security at $426M and NASA at $315M."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Who are the largest contractors in the NAICS 561210 federal market?",
        "body": "TRIAD NATIONAL SECURITY, LLC is the largest contractor with $5.1B in FY2026 to date obligations. Other top contractors include NATIONAL TECHNOLOGY & ENGINEERING SOLUTIONS OF SANDIA, LLC with $4.5B and SAVANNAH RIVER NUCLEAR SOLUTIONS LLC with $3.3B. Additional major vendors are CONSOLIDATED NUCLEAR SECURITY, LLC at $2.9B and UT-BATTELLE LLC at $2.4B."
      }
    ]
